headline: Seagate Technology (NASDAQ:STX) Exceeds Q2 Expectations But Stock Drops
summary: Data storage manufacturer Seagate (NASDAQ:STX) announced better-than-expected revenue in Q2 CY2025, with sales up 29.5% year on year to $2.44 billion. On the other hand, next quarter’s revenue guidance of $2.5 billion was less impressive, coming in 2.5% below analysts’ estimates. Its non-GAAP profit of $2.59 per share was 6% above analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Seagate forecasts first-quarter revenue and profit below estimates, shares slump
summary: (Reuters) -Seagate Technology (STX) forecast first-quarter revenue slightly below Wall Street expectations on Tuesday, hurt by weak demand for its storage devices amid ongoing uncertainty in the personal computer market, sending its shares down 8% in extended trading.

headline: Seagate: Fiscal Q4 Earnings Snapshot
summary: The average estimate of four analysts surveyed by Zacks Investment Research was for earnings of $2.46 per share. The electronic storage maker posted revenue of $2.44 billion in the period, also exceeding Street forecasts. Three analysts surveyed by Zacks expected $2.41 billion.
